http://www.thehindu.com/news/cities/Thiruvananthapuram/Power-supply-regulation/article13983750.ece

The Kerala State Electricity Board will regulate power supply from 8 a.m. to 2 p.m. on Wednesday at Kaimanam and Amritha Nagar for carrying out repair work on a transformer at Karamana.Power supply will be also regulated in places that fall under the Poojappura electrical section from 7 a.m. to 6 p.m. from January 6 to 10, to facilitate capacity augmentation to provide uninterrupted power to Vizhinjam container terminal.Supply will be regulated from 10 a.m. to 4 p.m. on Wednesday at Nalanchira and Udayyannoor which comes under the Nalanchira section. There will be no supply from 10 a.m. to 5 p.m. on the day at Pattom and Plamoodu and from 9 a.m. to 5 p.m. at Peroorkada Junction and A.K.J. Nagar.